.an 5
----------
1. Ursprngliche Anschrift - an Hebich.
2. Anschrift Hebichs an Gundert. Dieser schreibt seinen Brief darauf und
___schickt das Blatt wieder (mit David?) an Hebich.
3. Ursprnglicher Brief.
.fo +

I beg leave to inform you that from various reasons, I have made up my mind
to come into your Religion, and hope you will approve of my resolution: but
as I am very poor and unable to work for my living and clothes from old
age, I humbly pray your Christian Sympathy will provide for my wants, which
charity will be rewarded by our Maker.
.fo -
                                 I remain,
                                   Reverend Sir,
                                   Your most humble
                                   servant
                                      FBilith

Cannanore 18th July 1844
.ns
